**who —** THERMODYNAMICS OF COMPUTATION — a life-science sphere — the life/hardware bridge

**what —** Information is physical. Every bit your laptop — or your brain — erases must pay a fixed tax in heat. This is the bedrock beneath all the others: why computing costs energy, and why the most efficient computer might have to be alive.

**where —** the bridge between life and hardware  Framework inputs: the living; the machine; the information; the limit  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** Information is physical. Every bit your laptop — or your brain — erases must pay a fixed tax in heat. This is the bedrock beneath all the others: why computing costs energy, and why the most efficient computer might have to be alive.

**how —** Crystallized from the public record of the science.

**◌ the mythos —** Information is physical. Every bit your laptop — or your brain — erases must pay a fixed tax in heat. This is the bedrock beneath all the others: why computing costs energy, and why the most efficient computer might have to be alive. where life and hardware become one question

